    • Constructor Detail

      • Innovator

        public Innovator(int processingPower,
         int m_size,
         int p_size)
        Create an innovator agent object with given M size and P size. The set M and P will be initialized only when Innovator.reset() is called.
        Parameters:
        processingPower - a non-negative integer, which indicates the maximum number of changes to a configuration
        m_size - a non-negative integer, which indicates the size of the set M.
        p_size - a non-negative integer, which indicates the size of the set P.

      • getLocIdWithOtherLocId

        public long getLocIdWithOtherLocId(long otherLocId,
                          boolean isCopy)
        If isCopy is true, copy the set of digits indicated by the set of P from the given other location id to the innovator's current location id. If isCopy is false, the chance of copying is 50%. Finally, return the resulting location id. This method does not change the current location id.
        Parameters:
        otherLocId - a location id
        isCopy - a boolean, true for direct copying and false for 50% of copying
        Returns:
        a new location id, which is constructed by the innovator's current location id and the given other location id

      • reset

        public void reset()
        First call Agent.reset(). (Initialize agent's location with a random position, update its corresponding performance, reset time stamp to zero, reset search type to null, reset partner agent information, reset searching information.) Then initialize the set of M and the set of P. Finally, reset the alliance processing power to -1.
        Overrides:
        reset in class Agent

      • startNewSearch

        public void startNewSearch(Agent.SearchType type,
                  boolean isToSearchTheFirstStep)
        Overload the method Innovator.startNewSearch(SearchType type). Innovator starts a new type of searching process. Innovator does the first searching step if isToSearchTheFirstStep is true. Search type of Innovator: M, P, MandP, Magain.
        Parameters:
        type - a search type: Innovator: M, P, MandP
        isToSearchTheFirstStep - a boolean

      • startNewSearch

        public void startNewSearch(Agent.SearchType type)
        Innovator starts a new type of searching process and does the first searching step. Search type of Innovator: M, P, MandP, Magain.
        Specified by:

      • continueSearch

        public void continueSearch()

        Specified by:
        continueSearch in class Agent

      • startAllianceSearch

        public void startAllianceSearch(int allianceProcessingPower)
        Innovator starts alliance search with the given alliance processing power. If the innovator is a Key innovator (with smaller agent id), it does the first searching step by calling Innovator.continueAllianceSearch().
        Parameters:
        allianceProcessingPower - a positive integer, which indicates the processing power of the alliance

      • continueAllianceSearch

        public void continueAllianceSearch()
        Key innovator does one more searching step in the process of alliance search. This methods increase the two alliances' time stamps by 1 respectively. The behavior of calling this method by a Value innovator is undefined.
